 that the relative position of asset-bands is stays the same - thus ruling
 out a significant redistribution of asset values (e.g.
 with enormous taxation).
 On one hand, the processes of accumulation and inheritance are assumed
 to ensure that the wealth acquired within such bands is stable over time,
 but a certain mobility for all participans in the economy is allowed to
 assist inclusion, fairness and stability across the bands.
 In other words, every one in a higher assets-band having higher income
 would maintain a certain competition to admit those below the respective
 band to become a member.
 
